               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183010280032"></xptr>JOHN BRITTAIN. I am a hair-dresser - Mr. Frearson lives in <placeName id="t18301028-61-crimeloc338">Henry-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-61-crimeloc338" type="placeName" value="Henry-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-61-crimeloc338" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-61-off336 t18301028-61-crimeloc338"></join>. Between three and four o'clock in the afternoon of the 21st of October, Mr. Frearson came and said, "Stop that girl, she has stolen a veil from the door;" I pursued her, and saw what I supposed to be the veil - I took her, and said she had taken it; she said she had not - I kept her till the Policeman came; I then saw the veil in his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301028-61-person587">
                  GEORGE 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18301028-61-person587" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-61-person587" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-61-person587" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I went up and took the prisoner; I turned her round, and the veil dropped behind her on the ground - it appeared to drop from her person; it was half on her gown, and half on the ground.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301028-61-person588">
                  MARK 
                  FREARSON
               <interp inst="t18301028-61-person588" type="surname" value="FREARSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-61-person588" type="given" value="MARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-61-person588" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This is my veil - it has my mark on it; when I sell them I sometimes take the mark off, but not always - it is worth 10s.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The young man came and told me I had taken the veil; I said I had not - they both took hold of me; a little girl ran up with it in her hand.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t18301028-61-verdict339" type="verdictDescription">
